Tokyo -LRB- CNN -RRB- The operator of the crippled Fukushima Daiichi nuclear plant has given up trying to recover a robotic probe after it stopped moving inside one of the reactors .

Tokyo Electric Power Company -LRB- TEPCO -RRB- deployed the remote-controlled robot on Friday inside one of the damaged reactors that had suffered a meltdown following a devastating earthquake and tsunami in 2011 .

It was the first time the probe had been used .

Decommissioning work is estimated to cost $ 50 billion and will take years to complete .

TEPCO called the robotic probe an `` unprecedented '' experiment .

CNN 's Yoko Wakatsuki reported from Tokyo , Japan and Naomi Ng wrote from Hong Kong .

